The paper proposes a new class of games and studies them in the context of Bayesian games. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of strategies and algorithms, which are common topics in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of probability distributions, which is a topic in Statistical Learning (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the extension of the Prisoner's Dilemma game, which is a topic in Logic in Computer Science (cs.LG) sub-category.
